div.p:
I asked Dr. Cortina whether the President and the Committee had any major objections to raise to the draft bill prepared by Mr. Mersereau and Dr. García Montes in other respects. He said that
they had no such objections to raise to his knowledge. They considered that the draft bill on the whole was an excellent piece of work. There were two principal points, Dr. Cortina said, to be cleared up:
1. Whether it was in the opinion of the Bank necessary that the taxes should be sufficient to cover the amortization and interest of the whole credit in ten years;
